Umbral in Midgaard's deep levels notice what the city's surface records omit. The Gloamvault's shadow-archives contain records of the sealed warrants, Conclave transfers, and Ash-and-Iron administrative decisions that Continuity archivists have either deliberately omitted or sealed. From an Umbral perspective, the city's official human record is a document defined by its absences: who was transferred, whose classification was changed, whose civic identity was administratively erased. The Reckoning faction has cultivated Umbral archive relationships specifically because those archives contain what the official registry suppresses. The Continuity faction tolerates Umbral communities because their intelligence and legal discretion functions are genuinely useful — but not because the city has resolved what the Umbral's parallel records imply about the official account. Umbral living in Midgaard experience human institutional history as a record they can read more completely than the humans who produced it. The city was built above the Gloamvault. The Umbral were there first. This fact is not commemorated in any civic curriculum.

